            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "upstream_combined_diagnostics_typical",
                    "description": "Reproduces the upstream `TroposphericChemistrySystem` combined-diagnostic testitems at the TypicalConditions default scenario (test/test_combined_system.jl: `NOx = NO + NO2`:98, `HOx = OH + HO2`:121, `O3 Production Diagnostics`:148, `NOx Loss Rate`:176, `OPE Calculation`:204, `O3 Production Budget Consistency`:370). Pins all 9 combined diagnostics: NOx=2.75e16 (=NO+NO2), HOx=1.01e14 (=OH+HO2, HO2-dominated), RO2=1e14 (=CH3O2); P_O3_total/L_O3_total/P_O3_net satisfy the budget identity P_O3_net = P_O3_total - L_O3_total; L_NOx = k_OH_NO2·OH·NO2 = 1e-17·1e12·2.5e16 (the upstream-asserted 2.5e11); OPE = P_O3_total/L_NOx; chain_length re-exposed from the co subsystem. Upstream asserts rtol=1e-6 bounds and identities; re-asserted here at the tighter model rel=1e-10.",
